title: Paneer Herb Protein Roast — Low-Carb Edition 1
hydrationTip: Pair with 300–500 ml water to support low-carb vegetarian digestion.
method: Preheat oven to 200°C.
Slice paneer or halloumi and toss with vegetables, olive oil, herbs, salt, and pepper.
Roast until the cheese is golden and vegetables are tender.
Divide into four portions for batch prep.
swaps: Use cottage cheese as a topping instead of paneer.
Swap broccoli for asparagus or courgette.
Add chilli flakes or smoked paprika for additional flavour.
